[T1] Species derivation (first principles, D=24, angle unit pi/12):
  In-ring tile := every corner angle is an integer number of units.
  Regular n-gon: interior = 12(n-2)/n = 12 - 24/n units; integer <=> n | 24, n >= 3
    => n in {3,4,6,8,12,24}, interiors {4,6,8,9,10,11}. The 24-gon (11 units) IS in-ring
    and is included: 24-gon corner + 3*d13 dent = 11+13 = 24 is a legal 2-corner fill, so
    the regular-only exclusion argument does not carry over to star palettes.
  Isotoxal star n*a: point = a units, dent = 24 - 24/n - a units; both integer <=> n | 24.
    Proper star <=> dent reflex <=> 24 - 24/n - a > 12 <=> a < 12 - 24/n = interior(n-gon),
    i.e. 1 <= a <= 11 - 24/n. (n=2 gives an empty range, so n >= 3 is automatic.)
    => 3*{1..3}, 4*{1..5}, 6*{1..7}, 8*{1..8}, 12*{1..9}, 24*{1..10} = 3+5+7+8+9+10 = 42.
  TOTAL: 42 star species + 6 regular = 48 tiles = 6 + 84 = 90 corner classes.
  Sanity: star24's 5 regulars + 15 star species are a strict subset (verified by script).
  New vs star24: regular 24-gon + 27 star species:
    3*3; 4*{1,5}; 6*{1,3,7}; 8*{2,4,5,7,8}; 12*{1,3,5,7,8,9}; 24*{1..10}.
  Palette written: alphabets/palettes/star24full.json (48 tiles; star24.json untouched;
  famchars of shared species identical to star24, new species sP..sZ,uA..uP, 24-gon 'y').
